President Obama expresses the importance of providing relief to Americans who are struggling with unemployment and financial difficulties during tough economic times. He acknowledges the dependence of millions of Americans on unemployment and health insurance benefits, and expresses gratitude for the temporary extension of these benefits. However, he urges Congress to quickly extend these benefits through the end of the year, and also calls for legislation to support small businesses and increase job growth. The President emphasizes that his top priority is ensuring that every American who wants a job is able to find one.